BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Untitled-design-9.jpg
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260715T054521Z
DESCRIPTION:Trees are more than sources of shade\, beauty and sustenance—they are living indicators of environmental change. Join us for an engaging workshop with SeasonWatch\, a pan-India citizen science initiative that studies the seasonal cycles of trees to better understand the impacts of climate change. Through observing the leaves\, flowers and fruits of common trees\, participants will discover how seasonal changes reveal shifts in our environment and why long-term monitoring is vital for climate research.\n\nThe workshop with Sayee Girdhari combines both indoor and outdoor learning\, offering insight into how everyday observations can contribute to scientific research.\n\n\n\nThis event is in conjunction with our ongoing permanent exhibition Beneath the Turning Sky. \n\n\n\n
DTEND:20260719T073000Z
DTSTART:20260719T043000Z
SUMMARY:Trees as Climate Witness
UID:1331@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/trees-as-climate-witness/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Screenshot-2026-07-15-200131.png
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260715T143249Z
DESCRIPTION:A Moving Line gathers more than 250 works to trace how India has told stories in sequence across fifteen hundred years. Come\, witness both the creation of new visual identities and the evolution of a nation through a vast body of works across time and space as Khushi Bansal from the MAP team guides you through it. Follow a single line from a temple wall in Bengaluru to the touchscreen\, and watch a country tell its stories.\n\nThis programme is part of the celebration of the opening of A Moving Line: 1500 Years of Indian Visual Storytelling. \n\nThis exhibition is curated by the artist Amruta Patil\, in partnership with the Cité internationale de la bande dessinée et de l’image (CIBDI)\, Angoulême. It is supported by the Embassy of France in India and the French Institute in India within the larger framework of the Desibel project — an Indo-French initiative that brings together creators\, institutions and communities to shape the future of comics and visual storytelling within India’s animation\, visual effects\, gaming\, comics\, and extended reality (AVGC-XR) sector. A version of the exhibition will travel to Angoulême in January 2027 for the opening of the Angoulême International Comics Festival\, marking a milestone in the history of Indian comics in France.
DTEND:20260726T083000Z
DTSTART:20260726T073000Z
SUMMARY:Panels\, Pages and Presentations
UID:1343@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/panels-pages-and-presentations/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Website-cover-images-new-2025-05-02T115226.170.png
CATEGORIES:Film Screenings,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260714T070149Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening of short film screenings\, curated by Deepthi\, that bring into focus stories of neurodivergent identity\, resilience\, and authentic connection. Through intimate and thought-provoking narratives\, these films explore the realities of neurodivergent lives and the parents of neurodivergent children.\n\nSpanning diverse parental experiences\, the screenings invite audiences to engage with stories that challenge stigma through the power of storytelling. These films offer a window into the complex inner worlds that exist beyond labels\, celebrating the creativity and unique perspectives that come with thinking differently and embracing acceptance.\n\nThe programme aims to create space for dialogue grounded in understanding\, mutual support\, and the quiet power of shared experience. Whether you are neurodivergent yourself or seeking to understand better\, this evening is a celebration of the struggle\, acceptance\, and brilliance of neurodivergent individuals and their caregivers/parents.
DTEND:20260719T113000Z
DTSTART:20260719T093000Z
SUMMARY:Stories of Neurodivergence: A Short Film Screenings
UID:1339@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/stories-of-neurodivergence-a-short-film-screenings/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Screenshot-2026-07-15-192302.png
CATEGORIES:Panel Discussion,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260715T135514Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Panels from Will to Live by Mia Jose\nComic artist Mia Jose and graphic novelist Simon Lamouret will converse about their experiences and the inspirations that led them to create their works. This session focuses on identity\, culture and the city\, drawing on their individual practices and the spaces their works are rooted in. The notion of city is rooted in some of their works\, which helps us see a space as one’s company\, a space of constant changes and as identity. Get to know about their thought processes\, artistic inspirations and how the country they grew up in influenced their works. \n\nThis programme is part of the celebration of the opening of A Moving Line: 1500 Years of Indian Visual Storytelling.\n\nThis exhibition is curated by the artist Amruta Patil\, in partnership with the Cité internationale de la bande dessinée et de l’image (CIBDI)\, Angoulême. It is supported by the Embassy of France in India and the French Institute in India within the larger framework of the Desibel project — an Indo-French initiative that brings together creators\, institutions and communities to shape the future of comics and visual storytelling within India’s animation\, visual effects\, gaming\, comics\, and extended reality (AVGC-XR) sector. A version of the exhibition will travel to Angoulême in January 2027 for the opening of the Angoulême International Comics Festival\, marking a milestone in the history of Indian comics in France.
DTEND:20260725T123000Z
DTSTART:20260725T113000Z
